WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.440
not have a Bible readily available for them

00:00:03.440 --> 00:00:06.519
in their own language, people that need to share the Bible,

00:00:06.519 --> 00:00:09.000
folks that only have parts of a Bible.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.079
And I'm so thankful to have a Bible, amen.

00:00:12.079 --> 00:00:15.640
And the Bible is just a precious book.

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:17.600
There's nothing like it in all the world

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:20.760
and it's God's word and what a blessing it is

00:00:20.760 --> 00:00:23.159
to have a Bible, be able to preach the word,

00:00:23.159 --> 00:00:26.200
be able to sing about the word and we're grateful.

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:28.440
Everything that you know to be true about God

00:00:28.440 --> 00:00:31.239
and about life, you know from the Bible, amen.

00:00:31.239 --> 00:00:33.400
And what a blessing and I'm so thankful.

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:35.520
Acts chapter number four this morning,

00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:37.279
Acts chapter number four,

00:00:37.279 --> 00:00:40.520
and to be looking at a portion of scripture here,

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:43.319
and I'm gonna kind of by way of introduction,

00:00:43.319 --> 00:00:45.200
kind of journey through chapter three

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.479
and into chapter number four.

00:00:47.479 --> 00:00:50.400
And so we'll just kind of reference a number of things.

00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:52.200
I'm not gonna read a bunch of the verses

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:54.240
as we go by way of introduction,

00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:55.680
but if you're familiar with the book of Acts,

00:00:55.680 --> 00:00:57.240
you know that in Acts chapter number three,

00:00:57.279 --> 00:00:59.599
a great miracle is recorded.

00:00:59.599 --> 00:01:01.919
And the Bible tells us that Peter and John,

00:01:01.919 --> 00:01:04.160
they're heading there to the temple.

00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:07.599
And of course, there's that man that is just lame

00:01:07.599 --> 00:01:09.839
and he calls out and he asked for help.

00:01:09.839 --> 00:01:12.400
And Peter looks upon him and he says,

00:01:12.400 --> 00:01:14.599
silver and gold have I none,

00:01:14.599 --> 00:01:19.160
but such as I have in the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,

00:01:19.160 --> 00:01:21.400
rise up and walk.

00:01:21.400 --> 00:01:22.959
And that man was healed.

00:01:22.959 --> 00:01:25.720
And the Bible says that he went into the temple

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.360
and he was leaping.

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:30.919
The Bible says walking and leaping and praising God.

00:01:30.919 --> 00:01:33.440
Verse nine of Acts three says this,

00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:37.639
and all the people saw him walking and praising God.

00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:40.120
And they knew, verse number 10,

00:01:40.120 --> 00:01:42.559
that it was he which sat for alms

00:01:42.559 --> 00:01:44.680
at the beautiful gate of the temple.

00:01:44.680 --> 00:01:47.599
Now this great miracle that is recorded here

00:01:47.599 --> 00:01:49.360
had a great impact and effect.

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:53.639
We find that thousands of people will trust Jesus Christ

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:57.400
as their personal savior as a result of this great miracle.

00:01:57.400 --> 00:01:58.239
Why?

00:01:58.239 --> 00:01:59.279
Because after the miracle,

00:01:59.279 --> 00:02:01.959
their people gathered together and guess what happens?

00:02:01.959 --> 00:02:04.760
Peter preaches the gospel, amen.

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:08.240
And often as you study through the book of Acts,

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:11.199
you find as you begin to read about the miracles,

00:02:11.199 --> 00:02:15.720
how God would confirm the word with signs following.

00:02:15.720 --> 00:02:17.639
We read that in the gospel of Mark

00:02:17.639 --> 00:02:20.320
and we find that the Lord Jesus Christ

00:02:20.320 --> 00:02:22.320
allowed for these miracles to take place.

00:02:22.479 --> 00:02:24.679
Some of these temporary sign gifts

00:02:24.679 --> 00:02:28.279
so that people would be open to hearing

00:02:28.279 --> 00:02:30.080
the preaching of the word of God.

00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:34.199
And the great company gathers together 5,000,

00:02:34.199 --> 00:02:37.320
above 5,000 trust Christ as their savior.

00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:42.320
And what a blessing to think about this amazing miracle

00:02:42.759 --> 00:02:44.880
and the impact of this miracle.

00:02:44.880 --> 00:02:47.199
We understand though that the religious leaders,

00:02:47.199 --> 00:02:51.559
they were angered and the disciples experienced persecution

00:02:51.559 --> 00:02:53.759
as a result of what was taking place.

00:02:53.759 --> 00:02:57.039
And as you get into chapter number four,

00:02:57.039 --> 00:03:00.639
you find that that persecution is outlined for us

00:03:00.639 --> 00:03:04.440
and the threatenings that are given to the disciples.

00:03:04.440 --> 00:03:07.279
It's very interesting as you read through the fourth chapter

00:03:07.279 --> 00:03:11.559
of the book of Acts, we find that on two occasions,

00:03:11.559 --> 00:03:15.679
the Lord purposefully uses this phrase,

00:03:15.679 --> 00:03:18.320
filled with the Holy Ghost,

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:21.880
filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:03:21.880 --> 00:03:25.080
We find the first reference in Acts chapter number four

00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:28.600
is with regard to Peter as they are called

00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:33.440
before the religious leaders and in verse number seven,

00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:35.919
it says when they had set them in the midst

00:03:35.919 --> 00:03:38.080
and so the religious leaders are there,

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:41.679
they set the disciples and they asked by what power

00:03:41.679 --> 00:03:44.759
or by what name have ye done this?

00:03:44.759 --> 00:03:47.559
And the Bible then says in verse number eight,

00:03:47.559 --> 00:03:52.279
then Peter notice filled with the Holy Ghost,

00:03:52.279 --> 00:03:54.800
said unto them, ye rulers of the people

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:57.080
and elders of Israel.

00:03:57.080 --> 00:03:59.559
He then begins to provide them with an answer

00:03:59.559 --> 00:04:03.960
to the question by what power or by what name

00:04:03.960 --> 00:04:05.080
have you done this?

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:08.360
In verse nine, if we this day be examined

00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:11.320
of the good deed done to the impotent man

00:04:11.320 --> 00:04:13.399
by what means he has made whole.

00:04:13.399 --> 00:04:15.839
So that's the miracle of chapter three.

00:04:16.839 --> 00:04:18.320
The Bible says in verse number 10,

00:04:18.320 --> 00:04:21.640
be it known unto, notice what he says,

00:04:21.640 --> 00:04:26.640
be it known unto you all and to all the people of Israel.

00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:33.480
Notice that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,

00:04:33.559 --> 00:04:38.200
whom ye crucified, whom God raised from the dead,

00:04:38.200 --> 00:04:43.200
even by him doth this man stand here before you whole.

00:04:44.079 --> 00:04:46.119
Now that's some boldness, amen.

00:04:46.119 --> 00:04:49.839
That's the result of being filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:04:49.839 --> 00:04:52.679
In fact, the Bible will tell us in verse number 12

00:04:52.679 --> 00:04:54.679
that Peter will then say this,

00:04:54.679 --> 00:04:57.839
neither is there salvation in any other

00:04:57.839 --> 00:05:01.559
for there is none other name given under heaven,

00:05:01.559 --> 00:05:06.399
given among men whereby we must be saved.

00:05:06.399 --> 00:05:09.679
Now notice verse 13, these religious leaders

00:05:09.679 --> 00:05:12.079
that are interrogating if you will,

00:05:12.079 --> 00:05:15.880
the Bible says now when they saw the boldness

00:05:15.880 --> 00:05:20.279
of Peter and John and perceive that they were unlearned

00:05:20.279 --> 00:05:23.720
and ignorant men, they marveled.

00:05:23.720 --> 00:05:25.480
And then notice the end of verse number 13,

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:27.279
and they took knowledge of them

00:05:27.279 --> 00:05:31.239
that they had been with Jesus.

00:05:31.239 --> 00:05:33.959
We find that here the result of being filled

00:05:33.959 --> 00:05:35.959
with the Holy Ghost as the Bible tells us

00:05:35.959 --> 00:05:38.559
in verse number eight is that Peter stands up

00:05:38.559 --> 00:05:41.040
and with great boldness, he answers those

00:05:41.040 --> 00:05:43.760
that are interrogating and he declares

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:46.760
the glorious gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:05:46.760 --> 00:05:51.200
He says with boldness that every single person

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:53.000
that was sitting on that council,

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:57.440
every single person in Israel needed to know the truth

00:05:57.440 --> 00:05:59.079
that he was going to declare.

00:05:59.079 --> 00:06:03.200
Furthermore, he says that there's salvation in no other.

00:06:03.200 --> 00:06:05.720
Aren't you thankful that Jesus is the way,

00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:08.040
the truth and the life and no man cometh

00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:10.600
unto the Father, but by him.

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:14.359
And we find that here, the first references given to us

00:06:14.359 --> 00:06:18.119
in Acts chapter number four of Peter being filled

00:06:18.119 --> 00:06:21.679
with the Holy Ghost after the conversation takes place,

00:06:21.679 --> 00:06:24.320
after the preaching is given by Peter,

00:06:24.320 --> 00:06:26.440
the interrogation continues.

00:06:26.440 --> 00:06:29.040
And we find that the threatenings intensify

00:06:29.040 --> 00:06:32.160
and the disciples are told to go and to preach

00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:35.959
or to speak no longer in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:06:35.959 --> 00:06:38.760
And we find that the disciples answer for we cannot

00:06:38.760 --> 00:06:42.320
but speak the things which we have seen and heard.

00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:45.239
Oh, that some of God's people today would have

00:06:45.239 --> 00:06:48.320
that same perspective that they say in verse number 20

00:06:48.320 --> 00:06:51.440
that we cannot but speak the things

00:06:51.440 --> 00:06:54.000
which we have seen and heard.

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:57.839
Oftentimes today in 2026, the Christians are silenced

00:06:57.839 --> 00:06:59.220
without being threatened.

00:07:00.559 --> 00:07:03.079
I don't know if you believe that, let me say it again.

00:07:03.079 --> 00:07:07.559
The Christians are silenced without being threatened, amen.

00:07:07.559 --> 00:07:08.679
These folks are threatened,

00:07:08.679 --> 00:07:11.440
they've already spent a night in jail and they're threatened

00:07:11.440 --> 00:07:13.519
and they're told not to speak any longer.

00:07:13.519 --> 00:07:17.040
And they say, we cannot but speak the things

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:19.679
which we have seen and heard.

00:07:19.679 --> 00:07:24.200
Oh, praise the Lord, we need some of that in 2026, amen.

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:25.679
We need to get so filled up,

00:07:25.679 --> 00:07:27.679
we need to spend so much time with the Lord

00:07:27.679 --> 00:07:30.920
as it says in verse 13, that they had been with Jesus,

00:07:30.920 --> 00:07:32.399
that it's just that overflow.

00:07:32.399 --> 00:07:36.320
We can't help but talk about how wonderful our Savior is

00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:37.440
and what He's done for us

00:07:37.440 --> 00:07:40.000
and what He wants to do for others, amen.

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:42.160
And we find that they eventually

00:07:42.160 --> 00:07:45.899
after being threatened some more, they are departed.

00:07:45.899 --> 00:07:50.000
And the Bible tells us in verse number 23,

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:54.239
that they returned, that they went to their own company.

00:07:54.239 --> 00:07:56.279
And as they go and they gather together

00:07:56.279 --> 00:07:58.119
with the other believers there,

00:07:58.119 --> 00:08:00.320
the Bible tells us that they prayed,

00:08:00.320 --> 00:08:02.160
that they opened up their voice

00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:03.600
or they lifted up their voices,

00:08:03.600 --> 00:08:05.399
they opened their mouths in verse 24.

00:08:05.399 --> 00:08:06.640
And when they heard that,

00:08:06.640 --> 00:08:09.799
they lifted up their voice to God with one accord

00:08:09.799 --> 00:08:13.279
and said, Lord, thou art God,

00:08:13.279 --> 00:08:14.920
which has made heaven and earth

00:08:14.920 --> 00:08:17.399
and the sea and all that in them is.

00:08:17.399 --> 00:08:19.000
And they will continue to pray.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:21.679
And we find that very specifically,

00:08:21.679 --> 00:08:24.559
a request is given in verse number 29.

00:08:24.559 --> 00:08:26.000
The Bible says in verse 29,

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:30.079
and now Lord behold their threatenings.

00:08:30.079 --> 00:08:31.559
Notice the request is this,

00:08:31.559 --> 00:08:34.799
and grant unto thy servants,

00:08:34.799 --> 00:08:39.799
that with all boldness, they may speak thy word.

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:43.080
We could spend time today looking at verse 29

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:45.400
and examining the request of the disciples

00:08:45.400 --> 00:08:49.479
and understanding how amazing it is

00:08:49.479 --> 00:08:53.479
that they did not pray for those that are persecuting.

00:08:53.479 --> 00:08:55.479
They did not pray that God would judge them.

00:08:55.479 --> 00:08:57.299
They did not pray that they would be removed

00:08:57.299 --> 00:08:59.340
from that difficult situation.

00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:01.479
No, in the midst of great difficulty,

00:09:02.320 --> 00:09:04.520
they simply prayed for boldness.

00:09:04.520 --> 00:09:08.520
They asked the Lord, Lord, give us boldness to what?

00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:11.359
To speak thy word.

00:09:11.359 --> 00:09:15.359
And we find that the specific prayer request is answered

00:09:15.359 --> 00:09:19.679
in verse number 31, when we read the second reference here

00:09:19.679 --> 00:09:21.840
with regard to the subject

00:09:21.840 --> 00:09:23.580
that we're dealing with this morning,

00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:25.619
being filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:09:25.619 --> 00:09:27.200
Notice in verse 31,

00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:28.239
and when they had prayed,

00:09:28.239 --> 00:09:30.640
the place was shaken where they were assembled together.

00:09:30.640 --> 00:09:31.799
Notice what it says,

00:09:31.799 --> 00:09:35.840
and they were all filled with the Holy Ghost,

00:09:35.840 --> 00:09:40.419
and they spake the word of God with boldness.

00:09:40.419 --> 00:09:43.760
And this morning, as we think about this statement

00:09:43.760 --> 00:09:46.359
that is repeated twice in Acts chapter number four,

00:09:46.359 --> 00:09:49.780
once in verse eight, once again in verse number 31,

00:09:49.780 --> 00:09:52.440
they were all filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:54.159
I wanna preach just a little bit this morning

00:09:54.159 --> 00:09:57.039
about being filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:09:57.039 --> 00:09:59.299
Last week, we talked about being free,

00:09:59.299 --> 00:10:00.119
made free.

00:10:00.119 --> 00:10:04.039
from the law of sin and death,

00:10:04.039 --> 00:10:06.179
and talked about the idea of being saved

00:10:06.179 --> 00:10:07.439
by the grace of God.

00:10:07.439 --> 00:10:09.199
And I'm so thankful to be saved.

00:10:09.199 --> 00:10:11.119
And at the moment, if you're here this morning,

00:10:11.119 --> 00:10:13.439
at the moment that you trust that Jesus Christ

00:10:13.439 --> 00:10:14.919
is your personal savior,

00:10:14.919 --> 00:10:16.679
something amazing took place,

00:10:16.679 --> 00:10:19.839
and that is that the Holy Spirit of God indwelled you.

00:10:19.839 --> 00:10:21.979
The Bible teaches us about the indwelling

00:10:21.979 --> 00:10:23.439
of the Spirit of God.

00:10:23.439 --> 00:10:25.059
The Bible tells us the Holy Spirit,

00:10:25.059 --> 00:10:28.479
the Holy Ghost is the earnest of our inheritance.

00:10:28.479 --> 00:10:31.679
The Bible tells us that we're sealed with the Holy Ghost.

00:10:31.679 --> 00:10:34.639
And I'm thankful this morning to understand

00:10:34.639 --> 00:10:37.559
the teaching biblically with regard

00:10:37.559 --> 00:10:40.599
to the indwelling of the Holy Ghost.

00:10:40.599 --> 00:10:42.139
But this morning, we're not talking about

00:10:42.139 --> 00:10:43.599
the indwelling of the Holy Ghost,

00:10:43.599 --> 00:10:46.679
we're talking about the filling of the Holy Ghost.

00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:47.779
And it's a different thing.

00:10:47.779 --> 00:10:51.519
It's different to be indwelled by or to be filled with.

00:10:51.519 --> 00:10:54.059
And we find that if you're saved this morning,

00:10:54.059 --> 00:10:55.559
if you've trusted Christ,

00:10:55.559 --> 00:10:57.599
that every single one of us

00:10:57.599 --> 00:11:00.959
would be able to stand up with assurance and say

00:11:00.959 --> 00:11:04.459
that I am indwelled by the Holy Ghost.

00:11:04.459 --> 00:11:07.039
The Bible tells us in 1 Corinthians 6,

00:11:07.039 --> 00:11:08.559
in verses 19 and 20,

00:11:08.559 --> 00:11:12.519
that our bodies are the temple of the Holy Ghost, amen.

00:11:12.519 --> 00:11:15.399
And we understand that truth and that principle.

00:11:15.399 --> 00:11:17.599
But here's the difference.

00:11:17.599 --> 00:11:19.199
Not every one of us can stand up

00:11:19.199 --> 00:11:22.559
and say that we're filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:11:22.559 --> 00:11:25.099
There's a difference between being indwelled with

00:11:25.639 --> 00:11:27.139
and being filled by.

00:11:27.139 --> 00:11:29.499
And so this morning, I wanna spend a little time

00:11:29.499 --> 00:11:30.799
looking at this subject.

00:11:30.799 --> 00:11:32.059
And before we jump into the points,

00:11:32.059 --> 00:11:33.619
let me just make one side note.

00:11:33.619 --> 00:11:36.579
In verse 31, the Bible says,

00:11:36.579 --> 00:11:39.219
they were all filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:11:39.219 --> 00:11:40.499
And then notice what it says,

00:11:40.499 --> 00:11:45.339
and they spake the word of God with boldness.

00:11:45.339 --> 00:11:47.179
And as we look at that statement

00:11:47.179 --> 00:11:48.339
at the end of verse number 31,

00:11:48.339 --> 00:11:50.359
it helps us to understand

00:11:50.359 --> 00:11:54.139
and really to be able to combat some false teaching.

00:11:54.139 --> 00:11:55.099
There's false teaching.

00:11:55.099 --> 00:11:56.699
Sometimes we get a little bit shy

00:11:56.699 --> 00:11:58.739
about preaching about the Holy Ghost,

00:11:58.739 --> 00:12:00.259
about preaching about the Holy Spirit.

00:12:00.259 --> 00:12:01.579
And here's the reality.

00:12:01.579 --> 00:12:03.259
We believe in the Trinity, amen.

00:12:03.259 --> 00:12:05.579
God, the Father, God, the Son, and God, the Holy Ghost.

00:12:05.579 --> 00:12:09.099
In fact, in just a little bit here in chapter number five,

00:12:09.099 --> 00:12:13.339
we find that there's a situation with Ananias and Sapphira

00:12:13.339 --> 00:12:14.899
and Peter's gonna call them out.

00:12:14.899 --> 00:12:16.099
Why? Because they lied.

00:12:16.099 --> 00:12:17.239
And notice what the Bible says

00:12:17.239 --> 00:12:19.179
in chapter five in verse number three.

00:12:19.179 --> 00:12:22.699
But Peter said, Ananias, why hath Satan filled thine heart?

00:12:22.699 --> 00:12:26.580
Notice what it says, to lie to the Holy Ghost.

00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:27.739
Right, is that what your Bible says

00:12:27.739 --> 00:12:30.059
in Acts five in verse number three?

00:12:30.059 --> 00:12:31.259
And so very plainly,

00:12:31.259 --> 00:12:34.580
we understand that God had revealed to Peter

00:12:34.580 --> 00:12:35.739
what was taking place.

00:12:35.739 --> 00:12:39.259
And we find that as Peter confronts there Ananias

00:12:39.259 --> 00:12:40.099
in verse number three,

00:12:40.099 --> 00:12:43.779
he tells them that he's lied to the Holy Ghost.

00:12:43.779 --> 00:12:46.059
We then continue to read in the portion of scripture.

00:12:46.059 --> 00:12:48.019
And we find that in verse number four,

00:12:48.019 --> 00:12:51.379
the Bible says this, speaking about the fact

00:12:51.379 --> 00:12:52.539
that they didn't give all the money,

00:12:53.379 --> 00:12:54.220
they didn't have to, there was no requirement to,

00:12:54.220 --> 00:12:55.179
but they lied about it.

00:12:55.179 --> 00:12:58.259
In verse number four, while it remained,

00:12:58.259 --> 00:12:59.259
was it not thine own?

